<br>
For those of you that dont know me..<br>
<br>
I am Ullric Littleblade, a level 55 barbariann rogue that came from SolRo, currently guildless.  Before I played on SolRo I had a halfling rogue on Fennin Ro, but switched after some time to SolRo, tried a few other classes before going back to rogues.  IMO, no class is quite as fun.  I've been playing rogues since release, and like to pretend I know a little bit about my class.<br>
<br>
I am a ring warden for <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> which means if you have any questions for me, please ask.  I harbor no ill will towards twinks (its counter productive, especially on AyRo). <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Sigh..now on to more...greed filled issues.  As I understand it, Saturday Scions is planning on killing the General for 3 of their rogues' epics.  I plan on attending as an invite of Friday, and also plan on doing some begging..<br>
<br>
You see, I am at the same point in my epic.  As a matter of fact, I only need kill the General to complete my epic.  I know it is bad form to ask an entire guild to help one person on a 40+ person raid, and I really hate asking anyone for help, but I feel I have some things to offer by participating more actively in this raid.<br>
<br>
Well, first off, I would be willing to go first on the raid, basically playing guinea pig for the other rogues attending, so they dont have to chance their epics until they know its a sure thing (hopefully).<br>
<br>
Secondly, I already have my Cazic Quill.  This is a rare drop off the General that is needed to complete the epic.  It is only attainable by either dropping off the General or completing the robes side quest.  A 4th General would mean a 4th chance for it to drop, allowing a Scions rogue to bypass their robes quest (which is a b*tch of a quest, collect an SMR, Kedge, Ishiva, and Oracle Robe, real fun).<br>
<br>
Third, as I have already said, its another General kill, allowing more interesting stuff to drop for the guild, including the Edge of the Nightwalker (1hs, 14 dmg, 25 dly, 8 str, dex, agi).  All I am really interested in is looting the one quest piece I need, the General's Pouch.<br>
<br>
I think (think), that once the raid gets rolling, more generals are not that tough, since the day spawns are available now.  Depending on amount of downtime, it could be a breeze, but again, I am not sure. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
